<a name="top"></a>
<p class="dateline">Thursday, October 30, 2008</p>
      
<p class="headline">Step Aside Hitler's Germans, Here Come the Spanish F1 Fans!</p>

<p>A Web site that has been set up in Spain against McLaren F1 driver Lewis Hamilton is filled with racist language.</p>

<p class="floatleft"><img src="http://www.solitaryone.com/images/articles/2008/10/MoorRacer.png" alt="Racist F1 fans; Moorish racer in Spain" 
title="Racist F1 fans; Moorish racer in Spain" /> <br /><span class="body8">A Moor in Spain</span></p>

<p>First let's get some things out of the way. All people are racist. If you are human, then you are racist (or "clannist," or nationalist, or believe in
"ethnicism," "tribalism," etc., or whatever else you want to label it). It's not a question of if, but to what degree. I postulate that it is a result
of evolution. Back in the primordial days, when the daily task for different clans and tribes was to attack and raid each other, those
who knew well enough to recognize and stay away from those of a different group probably had a better chance of surviving. Thus this 
instinct got passed on, and that is why I think this impulse is innate in all humans. (For a more scientific discussion of this topic, see this
<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/30/opinion/30kristof.html?ref=opinion" target="_blank">article on the NYTimes.com</a> Web site.) </p>

<p>Now moving on to the Spanish F1 fans. According to 
<a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/motorsport/formulaone/lewishamilton/3287052/Spanish-racists-target-Lewis-Hamilton-in-voodoo-campaign-ahead-of-Brazilian-Grand-Prix--Formula-One.html" target="_blank">
The Daily Telegraph</a>, some of them have apparently set up a Web site attacking McLaren driver Lewis Hamilton, ahead of the ahead of 
the season-ending Brazilian Grand Prix. Hamilton needs at least a fifth-place finish on Sunday to become the F1's youngest world champion. </p>

<p>The Web site is filled with attacks and other hate speech, much of which is racist. One post reads: "Half-breed, kill yourself in your car."
Others express hopes of Hamilton having a blowout or some other type of mishap or accident. Pictures taken at a testing weekend in
February showed some fans gesturing at Hamilton and a group in blackface wearing t-shirts that said "Hamilton's Family."</p>

<p>Now those of us who read some of the sports news that come out of Spain have reasonably come to the conclusion that a lot of Spanish
soccer and racing fans are racist. Even their sports teams have displayed racist attitudes, which I wrote about on a few occasions 
(<a href="http://www.solitaryone.com/?page=articles/2008/08/blogindex_200808#art_20080815">Apparently Spaniards Love To
Chink It Up<a>; <a href="http://www.solitaryone.com/?page=articles/2008/08/blogindex_200808#art_20080813">A New Ethnic Group Discovered: 
a Slit-eyed, Spanish-speaking and Tall People</a>).</p>

<p>So I guess I shouldn't be surprised by this latest bit of news. It's just that when one thinks of racist Europeans, Spaniards would not
be the first group to come to mind. Usually it is Germans, perhaps unfairly since the association is with the Nazis and Germans of WWII;
today's Germans seem to be much more open-minded as a result of their history. But now we might have to rearrange that mental model in our
minds, and when we think of racist Europeans, maybe we have short changed Spaniards and they perhaps deserve top billing.</p>

<p>Without repeating myself, it is interesting that these Spanish fans hate Hamilton because of his racially mixed background. As I 
mentioned in the <a href="http://www.solitaryone.com/?page=articles/2008/08/blogindex_200808#art_20080815">Apparently Spaniards Love To
Chink It Up<a> post, in relation to the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Pm_LbJTvTWA" target="_blank">famous dialogue 
between Christopher Walken and Dennis Hopper's characters in <b><i>True Romance</i></b></a> regarding Sicilians, since Spain was ruled by Moors
for a couple of centuries, many Spaniards probably are, like Hamilton, the progeny of mixed European and North African people. </p>

<p>Nonetheless, you can't override a genetic propensity with logic. God knows emotions trump logic.</p>

<p class="keywords">Keywords: F1, Formula One, Lewis Hamilton, Pincha la Rueda de Hamilton - Spanish for 'Burst Hamilton's Tyre',
racist, racism, Spain, Spanish, race hate campaign website, Brazilian Grand Prix, McLaren, Fernando Alonso, Felipe Massa, 
Circuit de Catalunya</p>
      
