<!-- META DATA: END -->

<a name="top"></a>
<p class="dateline">Thursday, October 23, 2008</p>
      
<p class="headline">In the "Real America," You're an Elitist, and I Don't Like Labeling People</p>

<p>In Thursday's part of a multi-part McCain/Palin interview with NBC's Brian Williams, Palin, in response to a question, said she doesn't like labels.</p>

<p><img src="http://www.solitaryone.com/images/articles/2008/10/hypocrisy.jpg" width="490" height="392" alt="Hypocrisy: National Association of Telemarketers.
Absolutely no soliciting" title="Hypocrisy: National Association of Telemarketers. Absolutely no soliciting"></p>

<p>In one part of the interview, Williams asks Palin to describe what she meant by "elite," and to define who the "elitists" are. The reason Williams asked
this question is because the McCain/Palin campaign has on countless occasions attacked their opponents and their supporters with the label of "elitist." She 
said that it was anyone who thought they were better than anyone else. When pressed as to whether it wasn't a particular background, education, economic class,
she refused to concede that she had implied just those things. McCain came to her defense and said that the elitists are located in Washington and New York.</p>

<p>In answer to a question about implying in ads that Obama was an associate of terrorists, Palin gave her standard answer about Ayers and how he bombed government
buildings. When Williams asked whether that classification of "terrorist" applies to those who bomb abortion clinics and those who set fire during protests, Palin's
response ignored Williams's question and returned to Ayers. </p>

<p>OK, so far, standard stuff. Now here's the kicker.</p>

<p><blockquote>
<u>Williams</u>: Governor Palin, are you a feminist?<br>
<u>Palin</u>: I'm not going to label anyone, or any part of America. I'm not going to label myself. </blockquote></p>

<p>Wow. I'm speechless.</p>

<p>This coming from someone who puts labels on everything: which parts of America are the "real America, pro-America;" "elitists"; patriotic Americans,
"liberals;" "feminist elites;" etc. I mean, most people at least try to hide or cover up their hypocrisy but&#8212;perhaps maybe because she's too inane or daft,
or whatever may be the cause&#8212;she just lays it out there for all to see, so blatant that even a blind person couldn't miss it.</p>

<p>I really don't know how else to address this blatant hypocrisy. All politicians, nay people, are hypocrites to some extent. But someone who can, with a straight
face, say in one breath who the "elites" and "pro-America" are, and then in the next say she doesn't like labeling people...</p>

<p>Critical words fail me. </p>

<p class="keywords">Keywords: John McCain, Sarah Palin, NBC, Brian Williams, Republicans, 2008 U.S. Presidential campaign, interview, domestic terrorists, 
elites, feminism, labels</p>
      
